lines.text: Ma'am, your husband Bernie, you didn't by any chance lead him to the lake blindfolded?
If I had a dick, this is where I'd tell you to suck it!
Murders and rapes in the city, people bomb planes, can the police stop 'em? No! But feed one little cow to a crocodile...
You're gonna stay right here until the police show. You're under full house arrest.
Thank you, officer fuck-meat!
[Upon finding a decaying toe]
Is this the man that was killed?
He seemed... taller.
I'm rooting for the crocodile. I hope he swallows your friends whole. You might want to arrest me for that too. Is that a crime? To wish the chewing of law enforcement?
I... I... I never heard of a crocodile crossing an ocean.
Well, they conceal information like that in books.
The lake is so black and still.
Yeah, we wanted to call it Lake Placid, but someone said that name was taken.
It's not a science trip.
Could you be a little more condescending? 'Cause I'm not real great with subtlety.
Something in that lake killed somebody, all right? I appreciate your trying to help. I'm really glad that you... brought the RAID.
There, that's better.
Ma'am...
Look, if you call me "ma'am" one more time I'll sue you, and with today's laws, it's possible.
She's good.
What'd Bickerman say?
Well, she didn't want to tell us about the second croc 'cause she was afraid we'd blow its head off.
Women's intuition.
[Hector Cyr is preparing to SCUBA dive to look for the crocodile]
I brought a pork chop for luck. Maybe you could hang it around your neck.
That's sweet. Maybe later you can chew the bark off my big fat log.
I'm rooting for the crocodile. I hope he swallows your friends whole.
You got to fire your big gun. Did it meet your expectations?
Overrated.
I don't do field and even if I did... Maine? I'm allergic to timber!
He bit me! He bit me! There's two! There's two!
I can count.
[the second crocs rears up out of the water and the sheriff blows his head off with the grenade launcher]
Back to one.

[after the death of a deputy]
I'm sorry about your deputy... whenever someone dies, I always feel like it's such a waste that I didn't know them any better.

[sarcastic]
I'm sorry for your loss, Hector.
That's not really what I meant.

[shaking his head]
His head was just... bitten off.

I used to have a recurring nightmare that I was headless. I'd be down on the ground looking up at my headless body, watching myself walk around the yard bumping into things, and my parents wouldn't let me in the house because they'd just bought all these antique lamps didn't want me to knock them over, the fuckers. Then the neighborhood kids came by, saw my severed head lying on the ground and started a game of kickball, and as I was being kicked around, I actually just felt grateful for being allowed in the game... What are your thoughts?
Tents were sent ahead. Should already be set up by the time we get there.
Tents? We're staying in TENTS?
I told you, two days we'd have to camp.
Yes! Camp! But I thought that meant Ramada Inn. I never heard tents! Will there be toilets?
Maybe we should just take you back.
Why? Because I prefer toilets?
Maybe I should just wipe myself with some leafy little piece of poison oak. And then I can spend the whole day scratchin' my ass, blendin' in with the natives.
Do you know how your husband died?
Oh yes! I killed him.
You killed him?
Oh yes!
Crocodiles can't swim in salt water.
Yeah, well, that'll be your little secret.
[Sheriff Keough finds two of his deputies digging a deep hole and gives them an icy stare]
He paid us. Five hundred.
It's a trap.
You accepted money from him?
We took a check.
[Hector Cyr is dancing with a female Deputy Sheriff]
Law enforcement is very dangerous work isn't it?
[She nods]
And you have such big, wonderful boobs.
Ha! Thank you!
Oh, my husband passed away. It's been almost two years now.
My department doesn't have any record of that, Mrs. Bickerman.
Well, I'm sorry. Incomplete records haunt me so.
What was the cause of your husband's death, ma'am? Do you know?
We don't mean to invade your privacy, but was he ill, was he sick?
Was he swallowed?
Sheriff, think about being rich. My parents had the added luxury of ditching me off at karate school on a regular basis. I *am* a brown belt, go ahead, take your best shot, take your best...
[Hank punches him in the nose, knocks him down]

[to Jack]
He said he knew karate.
You hit him.
I did, yeah.
Did he say "go"? Aren't you supposed to say "go" in karate? You're supposed to say "go"!
I'll sue you!
Go ahead.
You can't take a cow by eminent domain!
We just did.
We won't let her get hurt, Ma'am.
You're all cocksuckers! I knew it first, I just didn't want to say it!
What kind of backup do we have?
We?
What?
Well, I'm a little unclear as to why the museum would send somebody here.
You got a thing against museums?
Naw, I got nothin' against museums.
Ever been in one?

[after being startled by Hank and his revolver]
Jesus fucking Christ!
What the hell are you doing?
What the hell are YOU doing? I'm laying a spring trap.
I could have shot you!
This could end up saving your life, which is meaningful to you, because the longer you live, the more sex you get to have with your sister!

[comes running over]
What's going on here?

[about Hank, who'd been out for a bathroom break]
He's waving his little wang around scaring the shit outta me!

[holds up his revolver]
How big is *this?*
I gotta thing about mosquitoes.
I gotta thing about worms.
I gotta thing about ticks.
Uh, there's something I wanted to ask you. What's it like to be a woman in the woods of Maine? I mean, the guys don't turn all horny or anything like they did in Deliverance, right?
[She sees Jack Wells is listening]
Ahh... I knew you were there.
Hmm. Never been to Maine before, huh?
Oh, I have good hygiene, I'm not welcome.
[to a game warden]
I'm a civilian, not a trout - you have no authority over me whatsoever.
Who are you?
Hector Cyr, I said it once, lemme know when it sinks in, OK?
The tooth is in here.
Well that's... that's the morgue.
Yes.
Well, uh... is the dead guy in there?
That's where they keep 'em. Look, you want me to bring the tooth out here?
No. No, let's... after you.
Look. He's suffering. I get to be humane.
[Aims grenade launcher]
No! No. No, no, no look, he's trapped. We've done it. So what it's not a net but, but, but he's trapped. Mission accomplished.
Shoot him!
I've got more drugs. He's half dead.
He's half alive! Shoot him!
[the U.S. and Florida game officials finally show up]
We, uh, trapped him with our chopper.
[to the sheriff]
You know, sheriff, when friends or family say certain things, they tend not to register. So it helps to hear it from a complete stranger... you're fat.
His scales were oval. He's an Asian Crocodile.
Why... why would he come here? I mean, it's impossible. Asia. How would he get here?
Obviously some asshole in Hong Kong flushed him down the toilet.
[Kelly slaps Keough]
Quit hitting me!
Stop throwing heads at me!
We're saved! The museum in New York just sent us some additional backup.
Kelly Scott.
Jack Wells.
Hi.
Eh, some museum sent ya', huh?
What, are we all museum bigots in Maine?
She's rude sarcastic. You two should get along.
I will NOT calm down! This is the second time I've been hit with a severed head and I DON'T LIKE IT!
Let's not overlook the fact that he didn't eat me.
'Cause he just ate a cow, stupid!
We're doing the right thing.
[trapping instead of killing the crocodile]
You might think differently if you get eaten.
Gee, thanks.
She tell you that we had sex together? So vigorous!
I never had sex with you!
I'm horrible in bed. They never remember.
You're supposed to say 'go' in karate. You face each other, you bow, and you say go!
Yeah, as in go fuck yourself!

[slapping her cow to the crocodile]
Come and get it.
You hurt his feelings.
I don't care.
[to Keough]
Do you care?
No, he's an asshole.
Oh God, we forgot to pack feminine napkins!

[on the phone with the wildlife services]
Thank you, it's so rewarding to imagine my tax dollar finding its way to you, you fuckshit!
You are a saucy flirt.

[Kevin has just broken up with Kelly]
Hey.
Oh, hey Kevin! What's going on? What's happening? How's it goin'? How's your family? Good? That's great, it's so nice to see you. Fuck off.
Seems like we're getting lower.
That's what happens when I land.
Did you want to be killed by it?
You think I'm that nuts?
Hector, what you just did, there had to be some sort of death wish going on.
In ancient Malenesia people suspected of crime's would be thrown to the crocodiles. Crocodiles would decide. They would be the judge.
Oh, so that was you wanting to be judged out there?

Maybe I was, and so what? Is that too arbitrary? Better to be measured by my wealth? Better for me to get my self-esteem looking into the eyes of cheap sycophants craving a meal ticket? There was more honesty in those dragon's eyes. There was more dignity in those dragon's eyes...
Jesus, Hector cut the shit.
Aw, fuck it.
[Hank has been caught in another of Hector's traps. He hangs from a tree by his ankles]
I could probably cut him down but there's this odd look of mayhem on his upside-down face
Dig him up if you don't believe me Sherlock
Splendid lake, eh? Became a man on a lake like this. Rubber raft, Sophie Blake... She gave like a cow.
He thinks they're godly.
What was that?
ancient China, Egypt, Australia, Asia... Going back in history, crocodiles have been more worshipped than Jesus.
Is this supposed to make us take him more seriously?
No, it's supposed to make you understand him.
Come on, Hector. I know you're crazy, but you can't do this.
I need to see his habitat up close, Deputy Gare.
Then watch NOVA, OK? But don't go in the water, please.

[closing dialogue at end of movie]
Doesn't anyone "make a move" around here in Maine?

[opens the passenger door and moves his bag]
Get in.
You move a bag and that's it? That's your "move"?
Come on, I know a good bar where we can get some beers.

[gets in and closes the door]
Are the glasses clean?
Uhh... yeah. Are you gonna complain like this all night?

[gives him a look]
Start the car Jack.

[gives her a look]
I miss the crocodile already.
[they both laugh and drive away]
[end of movie]
